                    "id": {
                        "S": "e9bc10ae-7bf1-4db8-8932-748d6991e596"
                    },
                    "message": {
                        "S": "\n\n\nMark Waterice: Well, Jim, I understand that offensive linemen might not be the most flashy or exciting players on the field, but they are certainly some of the most important. Without a strong offensive line, a team's running game suffers, and their quarterback is constantly under pressure. That's why teams invest so heavily in these players.\n\nFurthermore, while it's true that offensive linemen can get hurt, that's true of any position in football. Injuries are an unfortunate part of the game, and teams have to be prepared to deal with them. And when an offensive lineman is healthy and playing well, they can have a huge impact on a team's success.\n\nAs for their personalities, I think it's unfair to make sweeping generalizations about a group of players."
                    },
                    "message_in_thread": {
                        "N": "3"
                    },
                    "updatedAt": {
